about.summary: Collection of plotting and table output functions for data visualization. Results of various statistical analyses (that are commonly used in social sciences) can be visualized using this package, including simple and cross tabulated frequencies, histograms, box plots, (generalized) linear models, mixed effects models, principal component analysis and correlation matrices,  cluster analyses, scatter plots, stacked scales, effects plots of regression  models (including interaction terms) and much more. This package supports labelled data.

name: r-sjplot
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "2.6.3" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-sjplot
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/sjPlot_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/sjPlot/sjPlot_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 5e7216718f421eaa6aa620ea52c3bbec8c532d23d5c03ffc716be65a6e9d3540

build:
  merge_build_host: True  # [win]
  number: 1
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{posix}}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-bayestestr
    - r-insight
    - r-performance
    - r-mass
    - r-broom
    - r-dplyr >=0.7.5
    - r-forcats
    - r-ggeffects >=0.7.0
    - r-ggplot2 >=2.2.1
    - r-glmmtmb
    - r-knitr
    - r-lme4 >=1.1_12
    - r-magrittr
    - r-modelr
    - r-nlme
    - r-psych
    - r-purrr
    - r-rlang
    - r-scales
    - r-sjlabelled >=1.0.14
    - r-sjmisc >=2.7.6
    - r-sjstats >=0.17.2
    - r-tidyr >=0.7.0
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-bayestestr
    - r-insight
    - r-performance
    - r-mass
    - r-broom
    - r-dplyr >=0.7.5
    - r-forcats
    - r-ggeffects >=0.7.0
    - r-ggplot2 >=2.2.1
    - r-glmmtmb
    - r-knitr
    - r-lme4 >=1.1_12
    - r-magrittr
    - r-modelr
    - r-nlme
    - r-psych
    - r-purrr
    - r-rlang
    - r-scales
    - r-sjlabelled >=1.0.14
    - r-sjmisc >=2.7.6
    - r-sjstats >=0.17.2
    - r-tidyr >=0.7.0

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('sjPlot')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('sjPlot')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://strengejacke.github.io/sjPlot/
  license: GPL-3
  summary: Collection of plotting and table output functions for data visualization. Results
    of various statistical analyses (that are commonly used in social sciences) can
    be visualized using this package, including simple and cross tabulated frequencies,
    histograms, box plots, (generalized) linear models, mixed effects models, principal
    component analysis and correlation matrices,  cluster analyses, scatter plots, stacked
    scales, effects plots of regression  models (including interaction terms) and much
    more. This package supports labelled data.
  license_family: GPL3
  license_file: '{{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-3'

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
    - ccwang002
